      "id": "1krq5uw39",
      "questionNumber": 8,
      "questionText": "<picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1krq7wg1s/535c6017-2e72-4bef-9972-f452d33334f2/f2a08400-f122-11eb-a221-f3b1f28d3393/file-1krq7wg1t-320w.jpg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 500px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1krq7wg1s/535c6017-2e72-4bef-9972-f452d33334f2/f2a08400-f122-11eb-a221-f3b1f28d3393/file-1krq7wg1t-500w.jpg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 680px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1krq7wg1s/535c6017-2e72-4bef-9972-f452d33334f2/f2a08400-f122-11eb-a221-f3b1f28d3393/file-1krq7wg1t-680w.jpg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/1krq7wg1s/535c6017-2e72-4bef-9972-f452d33334f2/f2a08400-f122-11eb-a221-f3b1f28d3393/file-1krq7wg1t.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 20th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 193 English\"></picture><br>Among the given species the Resonance stabilised carbocations are :",
