      "solution": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l2ppljtc/05b6a760-1bb2-4ab6-8ad1-5b3cdba93626/c07a7900-caa1-11ec-9875-97c40a5b0f9a/file-1l2ppljtd.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l2ppljtc/05b6a760-1bb2-4ab6-8ad1-5b3cdba93626/c07a7900-caa1-11ec-9875-97c40a5b0f9a/file-1l2ppljtd.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 20th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 193 English Explanation\">\n\n<p>For resonance positive charged carbon atom ( Name it carbon 1) should be connected with the carbon atom( Name it carbon 2) using only sigma bond. Then carbon 2 should attach with another carbon with double bond. Here you can see (A) and (B) satisfies this situation but (C) and (D) don’t satisfy the situation.</p>",
