    {
      "id": "1lguzrwva",
      "questionNumber": 10,
      "questionText": "<p>Thin layer chromatography of a mixture shows the following observation:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lgvevsvn/9f6b1a8c-7da4-4009-b8ec-456f29f585ef/945a4b40-e2ef-11ed-b29f-636b60af9e14/file-1lgvevsvo.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lgvevsvn/9f6b1a8c-7da4-4009-b8ec-456f29f585ef/945a4b40-e2ef-11ed-b29f-636b60af9e14/file-1lgvevsvo.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2023 (Online) 11th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 128 English\"></p>\n<p>The correct order of elution in the silica gel column chromatography is</p>",
